---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout>
  {/* HERO */}
  <section class="mb-12">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Autonomous Rover for Disk Transport</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 max-w-3xl">
          Autonomous rover that navigates a constrained course, collects and stacks disk-shaped objects,
          climbs a ramp, and delivers them to a designated drop-off location using camera-based perception
          and closed-loop control.
        </p>

        <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-5">
          <li class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-sm">ROS 2</li>
          <li class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-sm">Ubuntu 20.04</li>
          <li class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-sm">OpenCV + cv_bridge</li>
          <li class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-sm">Python</li>
          <li class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-sm">Controls (PID)</li>
          <li class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-sm">Raspberry Pi</li>
          <li class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-sm">Arduino</li>
          <li class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-md text-sm">SolidWorks</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      {/* HERO MEDIA */}
      <div class="rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden w-full">
        <video
          class="w-full h-auto"
          autoplay
          muted
          loop
          playsinline
          preload="metadata"
          poster="/images/autonomous-rover/hero-poster.jpg"
        >
          <source src="/images/autonomous-rover/hero.webm" type="video/webm" />
          <source src="/images/autonomous-rover/hero.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          {/* Fallback for ancient browsers */}
          <img
            src="/images/autonomous-rover/rover-hero.jpg"
            alt="Autonomous rover prototype transporting disks"
            class="w-full h-auto"
          />
        </video>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* PROBLEM + CONSTRAINTS */}
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Problem & Constraints</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start">
      <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-3">
        <p>
          The rover must autonomously traverse a course (curves, ramp, obstacles), collect and stack disks,
          and drop them off in a specified order under strict size and robustness constraints.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li>Must fit within a compact volume and remain functional after a short drop test.</li>
          <li>Line-following navigation through curved segments and a ramp.</li>
          <li>Pick up and transport at least two disks; bonus for three.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <img
        src="/images/autonomous-rover/venue-diagram.png"
        alt="Testing venue diagram showing start, pickup, ramp, and drop-off zones"
        class="rounded-lg shadow-sm w-full"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* SYSTEM OVERVIEW */}
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">System Overview</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start">
      <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-3">
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li><span class="font-medium">robot_ws:</span> Raspberry Pi running Ubuntu 20.04 + ROS 2 Humble.</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium">dev_ws:</span> laptop on the same network for monitoring/debug (SSH + ROS tools).</li>
          <li>ROS 2 nodes communicate via topics (e.g., <code>/image_in</code>, <code>/line_position</code>, <code>/cmd_vel</code>).</li>
          <li>Camera stream viewable via <code>rqt_image_view</code>; logs streamed to dev terminal.</li>
          <li>Arduino handles low-level actuation; ROS-to-Arduino bridge handles read/write for encoders + motor commands.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <img
          src="/images/autonomous-rover/ros-network-architecture.png"
          alt="ROS 2 communication network between robot_ws and dev_ws"
          class="rounded-lg shadow-sm w-full"
        />
        <img
          src="/images/autonomous-rover/electronics-schematic.png"
          alt="Electronics schematic and wiring overview"
          class="rounded-lg shadow-sm w-full"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* MECHANICAL */}
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Mechanical Design</h2>

     <!-- Your existing 3 mechanical cards below -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="rounded-lg border bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Chassis</h3>
        <img class="rounded-md mb-3" src="/images/autonomous-rover/cad-overview.png" alt="Assembled rover CAD overview" />
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Modular layered chassis designed for stability, rapid iteration, and serviceability.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Basket Lift</h3>
        <img class="rounded-md mb-3" src="/images/autonomous-rover/basket-lift.png" alt="Basket lift crank-slider mechanism" />
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Crank-slider lift raises the basket for controlled placement at the drop-off platform.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Scoop Arm</h3>
        <img class="rounded-md mb-3" src="/images/autonomous-rover/arm-rack-pinion.png" alt="Rack and pinion scoop arm mechanism" />
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Rack-and-pinion style extension with servo control for disk pickup and unloading.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Key Specs -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start mb-8">
      <div class="rounded-lg border bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Key Specs (from report)</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li><span class="font-medium">Footprint:</span> 257 mm × 210 mm</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium">Wheelbase:</span> 210 mm</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium">Wheel diameter:</span> 64 mm</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium">Drive motors:</span> N20 6V 15000 RPM</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium">Arm actuation:</span> 2 positional servos + 1 continuous servo</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Mass / Weight Breakdown</h3>
        <img
          class="rounded-md"
          src="/images/autonomous-rover/weight.png"
          alt="Rover weight breakdown table"
        />
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">
          Used for motor sizing, ramp force estimation, and stability checks.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Motor sizing (torque / ramp) -->
    <div class="rounded-lg border bg-white p-5 shadow-sm mb-8">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Motor Sizing (Ramp Torque)</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
        To climb a ramp at constant speed, a first-order wheel torque estimate is:
      </p>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border rounded-md p-4 text-gray-800 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
        <pre class="whitespace-pre-wrap">
  F_required ≈ m g (sin θ + μ cos θ)
  τ_wheel ≈ F_required · r_wheel
  τ_motor ≈ τ_wheel / (gear_ratio · η)
        </pre>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">
        Where <span class="font-mono">m</span> comes from the weight table, <span class="font-mono">θ</span> is ramp angle,
        <span class="font-mono">μ</span> is effective rolling/friction term, <span class="font-mono">r_wheel = 0.032 m</span>.
        This lets you sanity-check whether the N20 gearmotor torque is in the right ballpark and how sensitive performance is to mass/friction.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* CONTROLS */}
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Controls & Autonomy</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start">
      <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-6">

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">ROS 2 Architecture</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li><span class="font-medium">LineDetector node</span>: subscribes <code>/image_in</code>, publishes <code>/processed_image</code>, outputs <code>/line_position</code>.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">FollowLine node</span>: subscribes <code>/line_position</code>, publishes velocity commands to <code>/cmd_vel</code> (<code>geometry_msgs/Twist</code>).</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Diff-drive controller</span>: converts <code>/cmd_vel</code> → wheel targets, closes the loop with encoders through ROS-to-Arduino read/write.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Differential Drive Commanding</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">
            For a diff-drive robot, ROS typically uses <code>Twist</code>: <code>linear.x</code> (forward) and <code>angular.z</code> (turn).
          </p>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 border rounded-md p-4 text-gray-800 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
            <pre class="whitespace-pre-wrap">
  v_left  = v_linear + (ω · L) / (2 · r)
  v_right = v_linear - (ω · L) / (2 · r)
            </pre>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">
            <span class="font-mono">L</span> = wheel separation, <span class="font-mono">r</span> = wheel radius.
            This mapping is where “high-level autonomy” becomes actual wheel motion.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Closed-Loop Motor Control (Encoders + PID)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li>Encoders provide wheel odometry (velocity/position estimate per wheel).</li>
            <li>PID minimizes error between desired wheel velocity and measured wheel velocity.</li>
            <li>Report gains used: <span class="font-mono">Kp=20, Kd=12, Ki=0, Ko=50</span>.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Computer Vision Pipeline</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li>ROS image → OpenCV via <span class="font-medium">cv_bridge</span>.</li>
            <li>Grayscale → crop/resize → threshold to isolate line.</li>
            <li>Morphological cleanup → contour detection → choose largest contour.</li>
            <li>Bounding box center → publish line x-position.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Special Cases (LineDetector Output Codes)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li><span class="font-mono">x ≥ 0</span>: normal following (use center error).</li>
            <li><span class="font-mono">x = -3 / -4</span>: sharp turn detected (box hits edge).</li>
            <li><span class="font-mono">x = -2</span>: intersection (box hits both edges) → stop / handoff to next behavior.</li>
            <li><span class="font-mono">x = -1</span>: line lost → recovery behavior (slow reverse / search).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Arm Control (pigpio + Bash)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li>Servos driven via PWM (500–2500 μs) using <code>pigpiod</code>.</li>
            <li>Pickup/dropoff sequences implemented as bash scripts with timed steps.</li>
            <li>Zone scripts interpret argument patterns (numbers/letters) to repeat motion primitives.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Wide image: contain it so it doesn't look broken -->
        <figure class="rounded-lg shadow-sm overflow-hidden bg-white border">
          <div class="w-full bg-white">
            <img
              src="/images/autonomous-rover/cv-steering-diagram.jpg"
              alt="Computer vision steering control diagram"
              class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
            />
          </div>
          <figcaption class="px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
            CV perception → steering command mapping (ROS 2 nodes + topics).
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <img
          src="/images/autonomous-rover/cv-thresholding.png"
          alt="Thresholding pipeline output for line segmentation"
          class="rounded-lg shadow-sm w-full"
        />

        <img
          src="/images/autonomous-rover/state-machine.png"
          alt="State machine diagram for rover behaviors"
          class="rounded-lg shadow-sm w-full"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* RESULTS */}
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Results</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="text-gray-700 space-y-3">
        <h3 class="font-semibold">What worked</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li>Reliable mechanical pickup and transport when perception loop was stable.</li>
          <li>Consistent drive behavior with encoder feedback.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-semibold mt-6">Challenges</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li>Camera lag / warm-up time created inconsistent autonomy performance.</li>
          <li>Integration across tasks was harder than individual task testing.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <figure class="rounded-lg shadow-sm overflow-hidden bg-white border">
          <video
            class="w-full h-auto"
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload="metadata"
            poster="/images/autonomous-rover/demo-pickup-poster.jpg"
          >
            <source src="/images/autonomous-rover/demo-pickup.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
          <figcaption class="px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
            Pickup demo
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="rounded-lg shadow-sm overflow-hidden bg-white border">
          <video
            class="w-full h-auto"
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload="metadata"
            poster="/images/autonomous-rover/demo-dropoff-poster.jpg"
          >
            <source src="/images/autonomous-rover/demo-dropoff.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
          <figcaption class="px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
            Drop-off demo
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  {/* LESSONS */}
  <section class="mb-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Lessons Learned & Next Steps</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
      <li>Add sensor redundancy (e.g., IR/ultrasonic) to reduce reliance on camera performance.</li>
      <li>Reduce dependence on platform height by adding a small lift DOF.</li>
      <li>Harden the autonomy pipeline for latency and reboot variability.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</ProjectLayout>